column5: for anyone that was interested, my jet boat restoration is comming alone great! , Just waiting for my new dominator jet pump from high tech performance comes complete with stainless steel inducer impeller and rated for 2000hp!!  Insert evil grin here!  I may have to but a blower for my BBF460...
Don't be showin "shania" them videos... or you know where that boat will be going! lol
da old lady just shakes her head!  this is my new harley~  Oh irish i need stainless rivets where can i get some, I want to replace the 3/8 wide aluminum rub rail..
Talking blind rivets?.. ie pulled with a hand puller? 1/8" diameter or 3/16".. and how thick do they need to go thru ?.. then I'll check my stock.
I called out the cougar just for you Irish!
As long as she's keeping her young lad in line Brad all is well !
ummmm I just went to show a friend the video and that's not the one i wanted to attach??  This is the boating video you must see!!
That video reminds me pretty quick why I sold my hydro many.. many years ago!  About them rivets....

My buddies dad used to drag race big block powered ski boats with vee drives. He's got 130 stiches in his right leg from a blowover during one race. His parachute pulled him free during the blowover but he carved up his leg on the gunnel as he was pulled free. He was still racing into his mid sixties.
Based on the video, my guess is that, unfortunately, some Darwin awards were handed out posthumously.
